## Project Overview

AeroPass (APS) is a fictional commercial airline passenger services platform that processes payment card transactions, supports SOX-scoped financial reporting systems, and handles Controlled Unclassified Information (CUI) under government charter contracts. Unlike a single-framework federal system, AeroPass demonstrates the multi-framework compliance reality of a regulated commercial enterprise — where PCI DSS, SOX, and DFARS obligations overlap on shared infrastructure.

This project demonstrates cross-framework compliance assessment skills: scoping, gap analysis, control testing, and translating findings into executive-ready reporting.

